      <body>Patch and tests pass, I'm just not sure if we should optimize ranges sum to use Arithmetic Progression sum. This way we would avoid instantiate and iterate through all the collection:

@@@ ruby
class Range
  def sum(identity=0, &amp;block)
    if block_given
      map(&amp;block).sum(identity)
    else
      (last - first + 1) * (last + first) / 2
    end
  end
end

Range.new(1, 4).sum #=&gt; 10
Range.new(1, 10000).sum #=&gt; 50005000
@@@</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Patch and tests pass, I'm just not sure if we should optimize
ranges sum to use Arithmetic Progression sum. This way we would
avoid instantiate and iterate through all the collection:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code class=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;class Range
  def sum(identity=0, &amp;amp;block)
    if block_given
      map(&amp;amp;block).sum(identity)
    else
      (last - first + 1) * (last + first) / 2
    end
  end
end

Range.new(1, 4).sum #=&amp;gt; 10
Range.new(1, 10000).sum #=&amp;gt; 50005000&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
